author: MelanieWuff
text:
Checkpoint:

I'm fighting a losing battle here, I think. Mother gone, Father not in the picture. I'm 20, living with my grandmother and likely burdening her with my mental struggles. I'm on some heavy meds and now that they've switched my medications, I'm not the same. I'm so tired but now cannot sleep without sleep medication, which doesn't give me restful sleep due to my antidepressants causing nightmares and the sleeping medication causing vivid dreams.
I'm becoming addicted to smoking. And smoking weed. It helps me ground myself but how can I go about life forgetting what I was talking about AS I WAS TALKING?
I've been having manic episodes recently, huge spurts of confidence and energy, then back to this sunken low that I'm usually stuck in.
I snap, I get upset easily and I cry literally if someone yells at me.

The only upside is that I have my boyfriend, but I can't even hug him yet because Covid restrictions are preventing me from flying to see him. The moment this ban is gone I will be getting tickets to see him.

author: Jakub N.
text:
Checkpoint

This is the first ever checkpoint I'm able to use. It's been a little less than two decades. A long time to go without saving a game.
So this is it huh
After years of not being left alone for a minute, of my personal space invaded, of me not being able to do anything I liked, after years and years of internal anger, madness, and sadness, I have my own room now. This feels... good. 
One day I'm gonna show them. All of them.  They're not ready for me. They can try to drag me down. I'm not letting them.

author: 山田健一
text:
海外ニキ達が書いたコメントを分からない日本ニキへ、

taiaさんがアップした動画、「とげとげタルめいろ」を観て、その曲から不思議な感じをして、セーブポイントにしていました。そして、この動画と他の動画もセーブポイントにし始めました。

その不思議の感じのおかげで、理由が別々なのかも知れないが、辛い過去から助け出した人達がいました。そして、その人達の話をこのチャンネルの動画にコメントで書き始めました。

僕の日本語が分かりにくかったらすみません。ただ説明しておきたかったです。ここまで読んでくれて感謝します。

author: Joe Mama
text:
Checkpoint ???+2?
I have reached a new checkpoint, few are left, many have been found already. When does my journey end? I'm neither a main character nor important, so why is it that I keep finding more of these?

My parents demand that I get a better job, that I go to college to make more money, yet all I want is to fade away, disappear from people's minds. All I wish is to not exist, and to most people, I don't. So why do I have people near me, why do I cling on to the past like I do? I can't explain anything. What even makes sense nowadays?

Save File 2
